OL,4,Cand loud noises expected in Port Talbot
OL,6,FThen extra sprays of water were
OL,7,Fcarried out to cool down the furnace.
OL,9,FAfter 24 hours, a 'blow down' process
OL,10,Fsaw workers stop feeding the furnace
OL,11,Fwith raw materials, including coal.
OL,13,FThey will carry on with the process
OL,14,Funtil all the materials inside the
OL,15,Ffurnace are consumed down to a certain
OL,16,Flevel.
OL,18,FIn the final stages of the process,
OL,19,Fthe bleeders are opened - which is
OL,20,Fwhen plumes of steam are expected,
OL,21,Fcreating whooshing noises.
